 {"id":"franken_networkx-tldi","title":"parity: reverse_view should support in_edges, out_edges, and degree APIs","description":"reverse_view currently has no in_edges(), out_edges(), or degree() methods, while NetworkX exposes all three on reversed directed views. This is a public API contract break: the view cannot be used as a normal directed graph in traversal and reporting code. Match the upstream edge-iterator and degree-view surface.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:08:18.773912216Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T18:53:33.055142132Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T18:53:33.053299124Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-tnl","title":"Utility Extras A: link prediction, attribute correlation, walk counting","description":"Implement ~10 utility functions: cn_soundarajan_hopcroft(G, ebunch, community) — Common Neighbor link prediction with community info; ra_index_soundarajan_hopcroft(G, ebunch, community) — Resource Allocation with community; cd_index(G, node, timestep) — consolidation-diffusion index; communicability_exp(G) — communicability via scipy.linalg.expm (more accurate than eigendecomposition); node_attribute_xy(G, attribute) — yield (x,y) pairs of attribute values across edges; node_degree_xy(G, x, y, weight, nodes) — yield (degree_x, degree_y) pairs; number_of_walks(G, walk_length) — count walks of given length via matrix power; mixing_dict(G, mapping, normalized) — generic mixing dictionary; local_constraint(G, u, v) — Burt's local constraint for a specific edge; recursive_simple_cycles(G) — find all simple cycles (recursive variant). Tests: link prediction scores match NX, walk count matches A^k matrix entries, NX cross-validation.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-22T17:34:39.067981419Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T22:38:06.501419213Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T22:38:06.500915309Z","close_reason":"Implemented 6 utility functions: cn_soundarajan_hopcroft, ra_index_soundarajan_hopcroft, node_attribute_xy, node_degree_xy, number_of_walks, recursive_simple_cycles.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["algorithms"]}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-tno5","title":"parity: all_pairs_dijkstra wrappers should support cutoff keyword","description":"all_pairs_dijkstra, all_pairs_dijkstra_path, and all_pairs_dijkstra_path_length currently reject cutoff with TypeError('unexpected keyword argument cutoff'), while NetworkX accepts cutoff and filters each source's reachable targets accordingly. Add cutoff parity across the family, including callable-weight cases routed through the existing single-source behavior.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T04:28:22.595382204Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T11:50:26.442383808Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T11:50:26.440473498Z","close_reason":"Already implemented: cutoff parameter works for all_pairs_dijkstra, all_pairs_dijkstra_path, and all_pairs_dijkstra_path_length. Test test_all_pairs_dijkstra_cutoff_matches_networkx passes.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
