 {"id":"franken_networkx-tp6j","title":"parity: equitable_color should accept FrankenNetworkX graph inputs","description":"equitable_color currently crashes on ordinary FrankenNetworkX graph inputs before it reaches the NetworkX coloring logic. On complete_graph(3), equitable_color(FNX, 3) raises AttributeError(\"'franken_networkx.Graph' object has no attribute '_node'\") while upstream NetworkX returns a valid equitable coloring; on equitable_color(FNX, 2), FrankenNetworkX raises the same AttributeError while upstream NetworkX raises NetworkXAlgorithmError about needing more colors. Preserve both the success path and the insufficient-color error contract on FrankenNetworkX graph inputs.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T14:13:34.238043501Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T14:13:44.317961115Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
